<paragraph blockId="5.[113,766,898,1274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[151,208,898,921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[244,478,898,922]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="montagnei">
<emphasis box="[244,478,898,922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Plagiochila montagnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common neotropical rainforest species that is recognized by terminal branching and ovate-lingulate leaves with a longly decurrent dorsal base, toothed ventral and apical margins, and strongly ampliate ventral bases with triangular teeth (HEINRICHS &amp; GRADSTEIN, 2000). The species is common in lowland forests and is only occasionally seen in montane forests. The specimen 
<emphasis box="[651,764,1090,1114]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Allioni 709</emphasis>
is chosen here as the 
<typeStatus box="[342,439,1122,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[476,551,1122,1145]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="nova">
<emphasis box="[476,551,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">P.nova</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it was illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="STEPHANI, F." box="[141,316,1153,1178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref9306" refString="STEPHANI, F. (1985). Icones Hepaticarum. Microfiche edition. IDC, Zug." type="book" year="1985">STEPHANI (1985</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 11214). 
<collectionCode box="[446,466,1154,1178]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
further 
<typeStatus box="[553,634,1154,1178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">syntype</typeStatus>
(Bomboiza, “frequens ad truncos in silva 
<collectionCode box="[450,478,1186,1209]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
